14/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Macedonian Army Chief of Staff Metodi Stamboliski and his Albanian counterpart Pellumb Qazimi met Monday (13 January) in Tirana and pledged to assist each other in army preparations for NATO membership and, to that end, hold joint military exercises.
The Macedonian delegation also proposed establishment of a training centre for peacekeeping and humanitarian units from Macedonia, Albania and Croatia.
EU security chief Javier Solana is expected in Macedonia on Wednesday to discuss the role of NATO's Allied Harmony mission in the country.
(MIA - 13/01/03)
